    <abstract>p. 94-100 about the "alternativ text" 異文 of Kumarajiva’s translation of the
        Amitabhasutra. There are three deviating text passages found in the Dunhuang manuscripts and
        the popular version. 1: the insertion 插入文 of 執持名號 (also known as text of 21 characters); 2:
        the passage about the two kinds of profitable [actions] 現当两益 securing protection by all [or
        the six] Buddhas 3: deviations in the Buddha names, which are also found in the
        《現在十方千五百佛名並雜佛同號》T#2905, 85: 1446c14-1449b21 as the "38 Buddhas of the 6 Directions" taken
        from the 阿弥陀讃一切諸佛所持之法經. </abstract>
